Ancient Mesopotamian astrologers devised a seven day week inspired by the heavenly bodies that wandered about the sky.  

The word planet comes from the Greek planētēs, meaning “wanderer”.  So by definition the Sun and Moon were considered planets to the Ancients.Their name is derived from the Norse Gods associated with the respective planet.  

The origin of Sunday is of course from the Sun in the sky.  Of the seven known metals, the Sun has always represented gold, irrespective of time and place.

The orbital motion of the planet correlates in sequence with its corresponding metal’s conductivity.The slower a planet moves, the less able its corresponding metal is to conduct electricity

Monday , ‘Moon-day’, is known as Lunes in Spanish, and dies Lunae in Italian. (lunar space craft, lunar eclipse). The Moon has always been associated with silver.  The word ‘month’ and ‘menstruation’ also have etymological roots in the Moon, in addition to having cyclical intervals of about 28 days.

Tuesday comes from Old English “Tīwesdæg,” after Tiw, or Tyr, a one-handed Norse god of dueling. He is associated with Mars, the Roman war god and also the Greek War God Ares. In other languages, the etymology of the days of the week is less occult(hidden).  

Wednesday is “Wōden’s day.” Wōden, or Odin, was the ruler of the Norse gods’ realm and associated with wisdom, magic, victory and death. The Romans connected Wōden to Mercury because they were both guides of souls after death.”  #Hermes Trismegistus is also long associated with Mercury.

Thursday, “Thor’s day,” gets its English name after the hammer-wielding Norse god of thunder, strength and protection. The Roman god Jupiter, as well as being the king of gods, was the god of the sky and thunder. “

Friday is named after the wife of Odin. Some scholars say her name was Frigg; others say it was Freya; other scholars say Frigg and Freya were two separate goddesses.She was often associated with Venus, the Roman goddess of love, beauty and fertility.

Saturday comes from the Anglo-Saxon word “Sæturnesdæg,” which translates to “Saturn’s day.” Sabado in Spanish, and dies Saturni in latin.  Lead is Saturn’s alchemical metal.

📍이번 주 성수동 소식 #위클리성수
BTS, 한소희 등장한 디올 레이디 전시! 몽블랑 팝업! 9월 첫째 주, 성수동 팝업, 전시 등 다양한 소식을 만나보세요.

1. 디올
LADY DIOR CELEBRATION. 디올의 전설적인 백, LADY DIOR을 기념하는 LADY DIOR CELEBRATION 팝업스토어. 프리즈 서울을 기념하며 열리는 전시로, 국내 상징적인 아티스트 24인이 재해석한 ‘레이디 디올’ 42점이 공개된다.
(9/2~17, 디올성수) #DIOR #디올 #디올성수

2. 몽블랑
몽블랑 라이브러리 스피릿. 크리에이티브하고 활기찬 뉴욕과 서울이 어우러진 카페가 타임애프터타임에서 공개된다. 익스트림 3.0 컬렉션의 다양한 레더 아이템과 만년필 시계등을 감상할 수 있다. 태극당과의 특별한 디저트도 판매 중. 네이버 예약.
(9/1~17, 타임애프터타임) #몽블랑 #MONTBLANC

3. 쿠첸 
쿠첸의 미토피아 팝업스토어. 진지(ZIN-Z)와 함께 다양한 이벤틀르 통해 '밥심온도'를 올리자! 미토피아 세계관 경험과 스탬프 이벤트가 펼쳐진다.
(9/2~17, 공간 와디즈) #쿠첸 cuchen_kr #공간와디즈 gonggan_wadiz

4. EQL
성수에 오픈한 EQL 플래그십스토어. '에디터리얼 숲'이라는 컨셉으로 2층 규모의 거대한 공간에서 펼쳐지는 EQL 콘텐츠. 아식스 팝업스토어를 시작으로 다양한 오픈 이벤트 진행 중. 
(9/1 OPEN, 에스팩토리 A동) eql_store eql_space #EQL 

5. 히로 x 휠라키즈
키즈 브랜드도 오픈런 필수? 키즈 스트릿 패션 브랜드 히로와 휠라의 콜라보 팝업스토어. 레이싱 무대를 컨셉으로 한 23FW 컬렉션 제품을 선보인다.
(8/29~9/10, 무신사테라스) #히로 #휠라키즈 hiro_store_ filakids 

6. 나뚜르
나뚜르 x 더필름 샘플링 이벤트. 나뚜르 포토존에서 사진 찍고, 신제품 성수 컬렉션을 맛볼 수 있는 기회. 현장 이벤트 참여하면 성수컬렉션 키링도 받을 수 있다.
(9/1~3, 더필름 성수점) #나뚜르 official.natuur #더필름 thefilm_official
